commit.message:
docs: Fix simple typo, achived -> achieved

There is a small typo in README.rst.

Should read `achieved` rather than `achived`.
Check on python 3.8 Support fro django 3.0. Close #222. Close #224

graph_transitions: fix list of layouts

Uses `graphviz.backend.ENGINES` to get the available list of
engines/layouts.
Handle case where transition.target.allowed_states is None
clean up Readme grammar and phrasing
fix for any/any_except target labels too.
Ensure nodes only reached by on_error receive labels for int choices.

commit.message:
Django 2.0 on_delete=models.CASCADE added to testapp model and tests,
edited tox.ini,
django-guardian warning ommited by adding AUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS to testapp.settings.
All tests passes.

Add a test to demonstrate issue with django 1.11

If model with state field has other fields that access their field value
via a property or a Virtal Field, then creation of instances will fail.
Add field to the signal kwargs. Close #133
Add support for Django 1.10 in graph_transitions
